<b>In August 2022, the World Food Programme</b>

239
01:09:16,300 --> 01:09:18,199
<b>cut rations by 75%.</b>

240
01:09:19,199 --> 01:09:21,699
<b>Refugees who once received 17 kilograms</b>

241
01:09:21,699 --> 01:09:23,566
<b>of food monthly now</b>

242
01:09:23,566 --> 01:09:24,866
<b>receive less than five.</b>

243
01:09:25,366 --> 01:09:28,466
<b>Since 1975, over 500</b>

244
01:09:28,466 --> 01:09:30,666
<b>Sahrawis have been disappeared,</b>

245
01:09:31,399 --> 01:09:32,366
<b>taken into secret</b>

246
01:09:32,366 --> 01:09:34,633
<b>detention without charges or trial.</b>

247
01:09:35,266 --> 01:09:39,666
<b>In 1991, Morocco released 300 prisoners</b>

248
01:09:39,666 --> 01:09:42,233
<b>who had been held for up to 19 years.</b>

249
01:09:42,966 --> 01:09:43,933
<b>The government had</b>

250
01:09:43,933 --> 01:09:45,966
<b>persistently denied holding them.</b>

251
01:09:46,800 --> 01:09:49,166
<b>520 people are still missing.</b>

252
01:09:49,966 --> 01:09:53,466
<b>In May 2021, Moroccan security forces</b>

253
01:09:53,466 --> 01:09:54,733
<b>raped a prominent</b>

254
01:09:54,733 --> 01:09:57,399
<b>activist named Sultana Khaya.</b>

255
01:09:58,033 --> 01:09:59,733
<b>Human Rights Watch and Amnesty</b>

256
01:09:59,733 --> 01:10:01,333
<b>International documented it.</b>

257
01:10:01,933 --> 01:10:03,166
<b>She's been under house</b>

258
01:10:03,166 --> 01:10:05,366
<b>arrest since November 2020.</b>

259
01:10:06,166 --> 01:10:07,466
<b>The world said nothing.</b>

260
01:10:08,500 --> 01:10:11,399
<b>brahim Hussein Leibeit was 19 when he lost</b>

261
01:10:11,399 --> 01:10:14,000
<b>half his left leg stepping on a landmine.</b>

262
01:10:14,433 --> 01:10:16,466
<b>He was trying to get close enough to the</b>

263
01:10:16,466 --> 01:10:19,133
<b>wall to throw a pebble to the other side,</b>

264
01:10:19,333 --> 01:10:21,666
<b>a symbolic gesture of crossing a barrier</b>

265
01:10:21,666 --> 01:10:22,833
<b>that shouldn't exist.</b>

266
01:10:23,366 --> 01:10:24,500
<b>When asked if he</b>

267
01:10:24,500 --> 01:10:26,566
<b>regretted it, Ibrahim said,</b>

268
01:10:27,033 --> 01:10:30,000
<b>"I would gladly lose my other leg if it</b>

269
01:10:30,000 --> 01:10:31,966
<b>would mean my country could be free."</b>

270
01:10:32,800 --> 01:10:34,033
<b>The ceasefire that held</b>

271
01:10:34,033 --> 01:10:37,133
<b>from 1991 to 2020 collapsed.</b>

272
01:10:38,100 --> 01:10:38,666
<b>Fighting resumed.</b>

273
01:10:39,300 --> 01:10:40,533
<b>The referendum promised</b>

274
01:10:40,533 --> 01:10:43,266
<b>for 1992 will never happen.</b>

275
01:10:43,766 --> 01:10:45,533
<b>Morocco won by waiting.</b>

276
01:10:45,933 --> 01:10:48,366
<b>They changed facts on the ground</b>

277
01:10:48,366 --> 01:10:50,399
<b>than international law could respond.</b>

278
01:10:50,966 --> 01:10:52,066
<b>And the world decided</b>

279
01:10:52,066 --> 01:10:53,166
<b>that was acceptable.</b>

280
01:10:53,833 --> 01:10:55,666
<b>Because in the end, this isn't a story</b>

281
01:10:55,666 --> 01:10:57,500
<b>about law or justice.</b>

282
01:10:58,066 --> 01:10:59,333
<b>It's a story about power.</b>

283
01:10:59,966 --> 01:11:00,933
<b>Morocco has it.</b>

284
01:11:01,399 --> 01:11:02,633
<b>The Sahrawis don't.</b>

285
01:11:03,033 --> 01:11:04,566
<b>And that's the only thing that matters.</b>

